---
title: Number Input
---
p.-text Number inputs are used to increase or decrease numeric values.

.m-alert.-bubble.-info
  i.a-icon.-sm--2.icon-circle-info.-text--info
  | This component requires Javascript

h3 Examples

p.-text
  | To render a number input, apply the classes <code>a-input</code> to an <code>input type="number"</code>.
  | For proper styling, number inputs must be wrapped in an <code>m-input__wrapper</code> div with two buttons.

h4 Base

.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__wrapper
      .m-input__wrapper
        input.a-input(type="number", value="0")
        button
        button
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input" value="0">
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>

h4 Disabled
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-form__wrapper
      .m-input__wrapper
        input.a-input(type="number", value="0", disabled)
        button
        button
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input" value="0" disabled>
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>

h4 Sizes
p.-text
  | Number inputs support a full spectrum of sizes: <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>,
  |  <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>.
  | The default size is <code>-md</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    each size in ['sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl']
      .m-form__wrapper.-inline.-mr--3
        .m-input__wrapper
          input.a-input(type="number", class=`-${size}`, value="0")
          button
          button
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input -sm" value="0">
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input -md" value="0">
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input -lg" value="0">
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>
    <div class="m-input__wrapper">
      <input type="number" class="a-input -xl" value="0">
      <button></button>
      <button></button>
    </div>

h3 Expanded version

p.-text
  | There is available an expanded version of the number input component.

h4 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-inputNumber
      input.a-input(type="number", value="0")
      button.a-btn.-icon
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-minus
      button.a-btn.-icon
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-plus
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-inputNumber">
      <input class="a-input" type="number" value="0">
      <button class="a-btn -icon">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-minus"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
      <button class="a-btn -icon">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-plus"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>

